{
  "stem": "24259.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as I talk to you, even though I talk English fairly well, I still do my thinking in Jewish.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's, it's an unusual feeling.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Enough times I've talked with some of my friends about it and with my family, same way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they find it kind of difficult to believe that this is taking place.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think just as a result of all the experiences, you just can't help but feel and think differently than most other people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish and Polish was our household language.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I still speak Jewish very fluently, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Polish, a little bit, but I've forgotten a great deal, primarily through not using it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I find that when I'm in the company of people that speak Polish, when I hear it spoken, it's still-- I can understand enough of it to get by.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember necessarily fear during the time of hiding, other than perhaps the crying part and being discovered.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some of it might be just because I heard some of these things being discussed with my parents.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I think after the war and from then on, I think there are certain fears-- certainly when I was a young child, I-- in, in a DP camp, as well as when we first came to the United States, I think I still have certain fears about being alone or left alone.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my parents never left me alone.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I never had a babysitter after the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And even when we came to United States, my parents used to take me wherever they went, be it day or night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I guess those are some of the fears, for whatever reason.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I never really thought about fear itself, but there were certain fears, obviously.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't recall any specific ones, no.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
